The tourism industry is the second largest source of foreign exchange. In 2019, tourism contributed 8.8 per cent to the GDP worth Sh790 billion. It’s responsible for 8.3 per cent of all employment and helps reduce dependence on other sectors such as agriculture.
 However, tourism is vulnerable to the threat of climate change. The causes and consequences of climate change resulting from temperature rise are global in scope, but they manifest themselves differently across the diverse regions of the world.



