Tourism destinations
According to a research by the World Tourism Organization (UNWTO), climate change will affect tourism destinations and their competitiveness.
Climate change is causing alterations in the ecosystems and natural resources needed to sustain the tourism industry, with impacts such as desertification, beach erosion, flooding, saline intrusion, landslides, coral reefs bleaching, rising sea levels, and health related problems.
At the coast, sea levels are expected to rise due to increased precipitation and flooding. Some studies suggest that as much as 17 per cent of Mombasa may be submerged in the near future. A rise in sea levels may create conditions of flooding, erosion, sea water intrusion and increased storm surges.



